  "_comment": "Browser DAST worker: allows execve/fork for Chrome subprocesses, filesystem ops for profile management. More permissive than API DAST worker — container-level isolation (namespaces, cgroups, iptables, non-root user, read-only rootfs) provides the primary security boundary. See docs/browser-worker-chrome-flags.md for compensating controls."
